burn(address).details: Burns LP tokens sent to this contract. The router must ensure that the user gets sufficient output tokens.

mint(address).details: Mints LP tokens - should be called via the router after transferring tokens. The router must ensure that sufficient LP tokens are minted by using the return value.

params.aAmount: positive to indicate token0, negative to indicate token1
params.aData: calls to with this data, in the event of a flash swap
params.aInOrOut: true to indicate exact amount in, false to indicate exact amount out
params.aTo: address to send the output token and leftover input tokens, callee for the flash swap

swap(int256,bool,address,bytes).notice: Swaps one token for another. The router must prefund this contract and ensure there isn't too much         slippage.

documentation.text:
